item.title: Rambo: The Video Game
item.dc:creator: Dotard
item.description:
It looks far better than Far Cry 1, memory can be deceiving. We might have a “Duke Nukem Forever” candidate here, game on an old engine having been tried to be pushed as far as it can get, hence the uneven quality.

If they improve the way destruction looks, make character faces more detailed so they at least slightly resemble human facial expressions before it releases, then it will be “passable”

For the gameplay, it looks fun, but nah, who am I kidding? Games like Serious Sam and Postal just aren’t in anymore these days
But since Saints Row and alike can still relatively succeed, then why not this one?

Read full topic

item.title: Rambo: The Video Game
item.dc:creator: Diabolical
item.description:
Dotard:

Not really PS2, more like PS2.5 or something.

You mean something like xbox graphics?

Bolteh:

To be honest. I think it looks like a fun game and the graphics aren’t that bad, they’re early PS3-level, but still fairly decent.

This simply isn’t an overly edited trailer like the ones we usually see from AAA developers. AC4 springs to mind, while the game does look great, the graphics shown in the gameplay trailers are lightyears ahead (this is also the case for games that already look great, like BF4, the trailers still show graphics no customer will ever achieve).

Well yes and to be honest I normally don’t care about visuals and graphics by the way, well except for screen tearing, just the gameplay is more important and that is true for the most cases by the way. Take a look at this years game shadow warrior for example, okay graphics, but the gameplay is really good. And let’s hope the developers of rambo better optimise this game.
Oh yes just one more thing. Let’s see what the gameplay is like on the full release version.

Ibanez:

seriously? I thought rail shooters died in the 90s

Rail shooters died in the 90s?

JohnWorfin:

No way, those are 1st gen xbox graphics

Alright let’s call it xbox graphics then.

Dotard:

The environments are decent, but the character animations look very bad, especially their faces.

I thought the character animations look better then the aliens colonial marines character animations.
